<body class="bg-[#fafafa] text-gray-900">
	
	
	
	<div class="layout-container">
		
		<div class="flex-1 flex justify-center">
			<div class="max-w-3xl w-full px-6 py-20">
				
				<!-- Title -->
				<h1 class="heading-font text-4xl font-bold mb-2">
					Cancellation & Refund Policy
				</h1>
				
				<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
					Last Update: 16 Dec 2025
				</p>
				
				<hr class="border-gray-200 mb-10" />
				
				<!-- Content -->
				<div class="space-y-6 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
					
					<p>
						This Cancellation & Refund Policy (“Policy”) governs subscription
						cancellations, renewals, and refunds for Whizard API (“Whizard”,
						“we”, “our”, or “us”). By subscribing to or using our Services, you
						agree to the terms outlined below.
					</p>
					
					<h2 class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						1. Subscription Plans
					</h2>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>Whizard operates on a prepaid subscription model (monthly, quarterly, or annual, as applicable).</li>
						<li>All fees are charged in advance for the selected billing cycle.</li>
						<li>Access to Services is granted immediately upon successful payment.</li>
					</ul>
					
					<h2 class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						2. Cancellation Policy
					</h2>
					
					<h3 class="font-semibold">
						2.1 User-Initiated Cancellation
					</h3>
					
					<p>
						You may cancel your subscription at any time through:
					</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>Your account dashboard, or</li>
						<li>By contacting our support team at <strong>contact@whizardapi.com</strong>.</li>
					</ul>
					
					<p>
						Cancellation will take effect at the end of the current billing cycle.
					</p>
					
					<h3 class="font-semibold">
						2.2 Effect of Cancellation
					</h3>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>Your subscription remains active until the end of the current billing period.</li>
						<li>No further charges will be made after the billing cycle ends.</li>
						<li>Access to Services will be suspended if no renewal payment is received.</li>
					</ul>
					
					<h2 class="font-bold" class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						3. No Refund Policy
					</h2>
					
					<p>
						All payments are strictly non-refundable.
					</p>
					
					<p>
						We do not provide refunds or credits for:
					</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>Partial use of Services</li>
						<li>Unused subscription periods</li>
						<li>Early termination or cancellation</li>
						<li>Downgrades or plan changes</li>
						<li>Failure to use Services after purchase</li>
					</ul>
					
					<p>
						Once a subscription fee is paid, it cannot be cancelled, reversed,
						or refunded under any circumstances.
					</p>
					
					<h2 class="font-bold" class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						4. Automatic Expiry for Non-Payment
					</h2>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>The subscription will automatically expire if payment is not received by the renewal date.</li>
						<li>Access to Services may be restricted or terminated.</li>
						<li>No manual cancellation request is required in case of non-payment.</li>
					</ul>
					
					<h2 class="font-bold" class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						5. Plan Changes
					</h2>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>Upgrades may take effect immediately with applicable prorated charges.</li>
						<li>Downgrades will take effect from the next billing cycle.</li>
						<li>No refunds or credits are issued for plan changes.</li>
					</ul>
					
					<h2 class="font-bold" class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						6. Exceptional Circumstances
					</h2>
					
					<p>
						Refunds or adjustments may be considered solely at Whizard’s
						discretion in rare cases such as:
					</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>Duplicate payments</li>
						<li>Verified technical billing errors attributable to Whizard</li>
					</ul>
					
					<p>
						Any such decision will be final and binding.
					</p>
					
					<h2 class="font-bold" class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						7. Suspension or Termination by Whizard
					</h2>
					
					<p>
						Whizard reserves the right to suspend or terminate access to Services
						without refund if:
					</p>
					
					<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
						<li>There is a violation of our Terms & Conditions</li>
						<li>Fraudulent, abusive, or illegal activity is detected</li>
						<li>Required compliance or verification information is not provided</li>
					</ul>
					
					<h2 class="font-bold" class="heading-font text-xl font-semibold pt-6">
						8. Contact Us
					</h2>
					
					<p>
						For cancellation-related queries, please contact:
					</p>
					
					<p class="font-medium">
						contact@whizardapi.com
					</p>
					
					<p class="pt-6 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
						© 2025 Whizard. All rights reserved.
					</p>
					
